title: TidGi Feature Handbook/AI Assistant/Vector Semantic Search
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Vector semantic search lets you find notes by describing what you mean in natural language, rather than relying on exact keyword matches.

!! Prerequisites

Configure an "Embedding Model" endpoint in [[TidGi Feature Handbook/AI Assistant/Configure External AI API]].

!! Building the Vector Index

In the agent chat, tell the agent:

```
Update the vector index for the wiki workspace
```

The agent will invoke the `wiki-update-embeddings` tool to generate embedding vectors for all tiddlers. A summary of indexed items will be shown when complete.

!! Performing a Semantic Search

Once the index is built, describe what you're looking for in a message:

```
Use vector search in wiki to find content about "how to use AI agents"
```

The agent calls `wiki-search` (with `searchType: vector`) and returns the most similar tiddlers along with explanations.

!! Notes

* After adding many new tiddlers, run "update vector index" again to keep the index up to date
* Results are ranked by similarity percentage; items above 70% similarity are generally relevant
